  "script": "If you or someone you love has a disability, there's a savings account that lets you invest tax-free, keep your government benefits, and grow real wealth. Most people have never heard of it.\n\nIt's called a CalABLE account. Qualifying diagnoses include ADHD, PTSD, anxiety, depression, and autism, among many others. You can contribute up to nineteen thousand dollars a year. The money grows federal and state tax-free in most cases. And balances up to one hundred thousand dollars don't count against your S-S-I or Medi-Cal. So you keep your benefits while building real wealth.\n\nStarting January first, twenty twenty-six, eligibility expands to anyone whose disability began before age forty-six. Millions of people just became eligible.\n\nI'm Rami Hindiyeh, financial advisor and founder of Finmentum. If someone in your family qualifies, DM me. This account takes thirty minutes to set up and could protect their financial future.",
  "script_raw": "If you or someone you love has a disability, there's a savings account that lets you invest tax-free, keep your government benefits, and grow real wealth. Most people have never heard of it.\n\nIt's called a CalABLE account. Qualifying diagnoses include ADHD, PTSD, anxiety, depression, and autism, among many others. You can contribute up to $19,000 a year. The money grows federal and state tax-free in most cases. And balances up to $100,000 don't count against your SSI or Medi-Cal. So you keep your benefits while building real wealth.\n\nStarting January 1st, 2026, eligibility expands to anyone whose disability began before age 46. Millions of people just became eligible.\n\nI'm Ramy Hindiyeh, financial advisor and founder of Finmentum. If someone in your family qualifies, DM me. This account takes 30 minutes to set up and could protect their financial future.",
